description:
Create EventCard at frontend/components/calendar/EventCard.tsx

## Visual Requirements (from mockup)
- White background, border-light, shadow-sm, 8px radius
- Category color bar at TOP of card (2-4px)
  - Orange: meetup
  - Green: startup/community
  - Teal: tech/ai
- Time display: uppercase, 11px, text-secondary (e.g., '8AM', '1PM')
- Title: sans-serif medium, 13px, text-primary
- Optional 'MEETUP' badge tag (orange background, white text)
- Hover: slight lift effect
- Click: triggers event_clicked_out

## Data Shape
```typescript
interface CalendarEvent {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  startTime: Date;
  endTime: Date;
  category: 'meetup' | 'startup' | 'community' | 'ai';
  venue?: string;
  neighborhood?: string;
  canonicalUrl: string;
  sourceId: string;
}
```

Reference: Spec Part 2, mockup screenshot

Create API client at frontend/lib/api.ts

## Endpoints to Support
- POST /api/chat - Discovery chat (existing)
- GET /api/events - Event listing (to be built)
- POST /api/search - Search with filters (to be built)

## Implementation
- Fetch-based client with TypeScript types
- Error handling and retry logic
- Response caching (TanStack Query integration)
- CORS handling for local dev

## Types
```typescript
interface SearchRequest {
  query: string;
  filters?: {
    timeWindow?: { start: Date; end: Date };
    categories?: string[];
    maxDistance?: number;
    freeOnly?: boolean;
  };
}

interface SearchResponse {
  events: CalendarEvent[];
  totalCount: number;
  searchId: string;
}
```

